The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Anil firm buys Vanco for Rs 327cr
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Anil firm buys Vanco for Rs 327cr
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, May 26: Anil Ambanis Reliance Globalcom has acquired UK-based network service provider Vanco for Rs 327 crore.        
	Reliance Globalcom is the global subsidiary of Reliance Communications (R-Com).        
	The Vanco buyout will help R-Com realise its target of being among the top five data communication players, Anil Ambani said in a statement.         
	Vanco is recognised by information technology research and advisory firm Gartner as being among the top five managed global network players with over 220 MNC customers. Its blue chip customer base includes Avis, British Airways, Siemens and Virgin Megastores.         
	The buyout increases Reliance Globalcoms enterprise customers to over 1,400.        
	R-Com said the buyout would add Rs 1,550 crore to its annual revenue and expand its managed network footprint to 163 countries. Under the agreement, Reliance Globalcom will pay $76.9 million to acquire 100 per cent equity of Vanco Group, free of debt, the statement said.                                                                                                                                                         
